---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Header from "@components/Header.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import { APP_STORE_URL, PLAY_STORE_URL } from "@scripts/store-links";
// import Footer from "@components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About | WrestleVerse"
  description="Discover WrestleVerse, the premium mobile pro wrestling booking & management simulator. Book matches, run your promotion, and experience live-called commentary."
>
  <Header />

  <main class="about-page">
    <div class="about-shell">
      <section class="about-intro" aria-labelledby="about-heading">
        <p class="about-kicker">About</p>
        <h1 id="about-heading">What is WrestleVerse?</h1>
        <p>
          <em>WrestleVerse</em> is a mobile pro wrestling management &amp; booking
          simulation game, where players run their own wrestling promotion, book shows,
          create rivalries, manage talent, and compete for ratings.
        </p>
        <p>
          Inspired by classic wrestling booking sims like <em
            >Total Extreme Wrestling</em
          > and staples in other sports like <em>Football Manager</em>, <em
            >WrestleVerse</em
          > combines deep simulation systems with a modern, intuitive interface designed
          specifically for mobile.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unlike many mobile games, <em>WrestleVerse</em> is a premium experience
          with:
        </p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>no ads</li>
          <li>no microtransactions</li>
          <li>no subscriptions</li>
          <li>no energy systems</li>
          <li>no pay-to-win mechanics</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Just buy once, and enjoy pure gameplay.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="what-do-heading">
        <h2 id="what-do-heading">What do you do?</h2>

        <h3>Book Shows</h3>
        <p>
          Book in-depth matches, plan angles, and balance crowd reactions to
          deliver the best possible wrestling show:
        </p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>
            book singles, tag team, multi-person matches, across a variety of
            stipulations
          </li>
          <li>
            outline specific spots you want to occur, just like a real wrestling
            booker
          </li>
          <li>chase show ratings and fan reactions</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Every booking decision affects wrestler momentum, fan perception, and
          long-term promotion growth.
        </p>

        <h3>Create Rivalries and Stories</h3>
        <p>WrestleVerse is built around long-term storytelling. Players can:</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>develop wrestlers over time</li>
          <li>create heel turns, betrayals, alliances, and redemption arcs</li>
          <li>build rivalries across months, or even years</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Run the Business</h3>
        <p>
          Running a wrestling promotion is more than just booking angles and
          matches. Players must manage:
        </p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>wrestler contracts</li>
          <li>roster morale</li>
          <li>finances and budgets</li>
          <li>championship divisions</li>
          <li>promotion popularity and growth</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Computer-controlled promotions compete alongside the player, creating
          a dynamic wrestling world that evolves over time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="who-heading">
        <h2 id="who-heading">Who is it for?</h2>
        <p>WrestleVerse was designed for:</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>
            wrestling fans who want creative control over their own promotion
          </li>
          <li>
            players looking for a modern alternative to traditional booking sims
          </li>
          <li>fans of sports management games like Football Manager</li>
          <li>
            players who enjoy sandbox simulation games and emergent storytelling
          </li>
          <li>mobile players looking for a deep, desktop-level experience</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          The game is approachable for newcomers of the genre, whilst still
          offering meaningful depth for hardcore simulation fans.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="different-heading">
        <h2 id="different-heading">What Makes WrestleVerse Different?</h2>

        <h3>Custom Universes</h3>
        <p>
          WrestleVerse features a growing library of community-created
          universes, allowing players to experience promotions and wrestlers
          inspired by modern, retro, and fictional wrestling universes.
        </p>

        <h3>The Commentary Engine</h3>
        <p>
          Every spot and moment you book, and even the ones you don&apos;t book,
          is called like it&apos;s on live TV by our unique Commentary Engine.
          There&apos;s nothing like this in any other wrestling game.
        </p>

        <h3>Modern Interface</h3>
        <p>
          Many management games focus heavily on dated-looking spreadsheets and
          menus. WrestleVerse delivers deep systems while containing a clean,
          modern user experience designed for mobile.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="platforms-heading">
        <h2 id="platforms-heading">Platforms and Pricing</h2>
        <p>
          WrestleVerse is currently available on the <a
            href={APP_STORE_URL}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">App Store</a
          > for iOS, iPadOS, macOS, and on the <a
            href={PLAY_STORE_URL}
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Play Store</a
          > for Android.
        </p>
        <p>
          WrestleVerse is a premium game with a one-time purchase price which
          varies across regions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
        <h2 id="faq-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>Is WrestleVerse similar to Total Extreme Wrestling?</h3>
        <p>
          WrestleVerse is inspired by classic wrestling booking simulators like
          Total Extreme Wrestling, but is designed specifically for mobile
          devices with a more streamlined and modern interface, along with
          innovative features that push the boundaries of the genre.
        </p>

        <h3>Is WrestleVerse similar to Football Manager?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes. Players manage long-term progression, talent development,
          strategy, and promotion growth in a similar way to sports management
          games like Football Manager.
        </p>

        <h3>Can I create my own wrestling promotion?</h3>
        <p>
          Yes. WrestleVerse features a deep and integrated Creation Suite that
          allows players to create a whole custom universe of promotions,
          championships, shows, and wrestlers.
        </p>

        <h3>Does WrestleVerse use real wrestlers?</h3>
        <p>
          WrestleVerse features original fictional content built into the game,
          but players can also explore community-created Custom Universes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about-section" aria-labelledby="credits-heading">
        <h2 id="credits-heading">Credits</h2>
        <p>
          Our beautiful landing page image featuring Maddy Morgan at PROGRESS
          Wrestling was taken by Matt Raven. You can find him &amp; his work on
          Instagram and X under
          <a
            href="https://www.instagram.com/matravenmedia"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">@matravenmedia</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <!-- <Footer /> -->
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    min-height: calc(100svh - 96px);
    padding: 96px 24px 120px;
    background: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .about-shell {
    width: min(100%, 980px);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .about-intro,
  .about-section {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-block: 56px;
  }

  .about-intro {
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .about-kicker {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-family: var(--font-rounded);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--btn-bg);
  }

  h1 {
    max-width: 820px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 11vw, 8rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1;
    color: rgb(255 255 255 / 92%);
    text-shadow: 0 4px 18px rgb(184 200 255 / 18%);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  h3 {
    margin-top: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.5vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: rgb(255 255 255 / 80%);
  }

  p {
    max-width: 820px;
    margin-top: 18px;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgb(255 255 255 / 68%);
  }

  a {
    color: var(--hyperlinks);
    text-decoration: underline;
    transition: opacity var(--transition);
  }

  a:hover {
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .feature-list {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(1, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 14px;
    max-width: 820px;
    margin-top: 8px;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .feature-list li {
    min-height: 56px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    border: 1px solid rgb(184 200 255 / 16%);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    padding: 14px 16px;
    background: rgb(255 255 255 / 4%);
    box-shadow: 0 16px 40px rgb(0 0 0 / 24%);
    font-family: var(--font-rounded);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: rgb(255 255 255 / 84%);
  }

  @media (max-width: 1140px) {
    .about-page {
      min-height: calc(100svh - 96px);
      padding: 64px 24px 96px;
    }

    .about-intro,
    .about-section {
      padding-block: 40px;
    }

    .about-intro {
      padding-top: 0;
    }

    p {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }

    .feature-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
